{
  "texts": [
    "The class salience map reveals that the network on the right-hand side utilizes geometric features from farther away.",
    "In contrast, on the left-hand side the network focuses primarily on the geometric features of the tooth itself.",
    "This discrepancy leads to misclassifications when the geometric properties of two teeth are quite similar.",
    "However, by incorporating features from surrounding areas, such misclassifications can be mitigated.",
    "In essence, these two scenarios highlight the distinction between predicting the segmentation mask of a particular tooth solely based on the tooth and its immediate surroundings versus considering neighboring teeth and gum tissue.The time required for a single forward pass through the network using a batch size of 2 with different numbers of layers and whether the indices are precomputed is shown in Table 5."
  ]
}